race.comment: INVISIBLE TARGET (3) raced handy and looked a chance but found one a little better when resuming over this distance at Warwick a fortnight ago. Drawn to enjoy the run of the race and is perfectly placed to take this out. RED CODE (2) is back for a second campaign after a five-month spell. Flew along in front to win on debut at the Gold Coast then failed in two subsequent runs. Trialling well and looks set to make a positive return. MARATHIA (4) has been settling back in her races and failing to make inroads of late. A step up in distance today might be the key to a return to form. BOWDARCIE (6) found the line well at Muswellbrook last time and will be more effective stepping out to today's journey.
